# Summary

These are APIs that are used *mostly* by the compiler - some are used *exclusively* by the compiler. I'm err-ing on the side of safety here by including things that the compiler touches so that we look at them.

At a high-level I plan on parking compiler-specific things in `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.CompilerServices` - similar to what the [BCL does](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.runtime.compilerservices?view=netframework-4.8). 

The primary thing to figure out with all of these APIs is whether there's any use case for a user to call them, or if they are purely an artifact of the compiler.

